## Page 9: Executive Brief – Single Printable Summary

**Purpose:** One-page executive summary (print-ready)

**Key Question:** What do executives need to know in 30 seconds?

**Layout:** Fixed layout, no scrolling, optimized for printing

### Top Section: Overall Health (3 Large KPIs)

**Layout:** Horizontal cards across top (33% width each)

1. **Attrition Rate**
   - Measure: `[Attrition Rate]`
   - Format: 13.2%
   - Font: Large (48pt)
   - Status Icon:
     - ✓ Green circle if <8%
     - ⚠ Yellow triangle if 8-12%
     - ✗ Red X if >12%
   - Subtitle: "vs Prior: +1.3pp" (with arrow)
   - Background: Light gray box

2. **Retention Rate**
   - Measure: `[Retention Rate]`
   - Format: 86.8%
   - Font: Large (48pt)
   - Status Icon: Same logic as above
   - Subtitle: "vs Prior: -2.1pp"
   - Background: Light gray box

3. **Net Headcount Change**
   - Measure: `[Net Headcount Change]`
   - Format: -45 (with +/- sign)
   - Font: Large (48pt)
   - Color: Green if +, Red if -
   - Subtitle: "Start: 2,450 → End: 2,405"
   - Background: Light gray box

### Middle Left: Top 3 Risks (40% width)

**Title:** "Highest Risk Organizations"

**Visual:** Table (auto-filtered to top 3 by Risk Score)
- Rows: `Employees[Org]` (Top 3)
- Columns:
  - Org Name
  - `[Attrition Risk Score]` (large, color-coded)
  - Key Driver (text field)
    - Example: "High new hire attrition"
    - Could be calculated field showing max of: new hire rate, experienced rate, velocity
- Conditional Formatting:
  - Risk score background (red gradient)
- Font: Medium size for readability
- Borders: Clean, professional

### Middle Center: Key Trend (30% width)

**Title:** "6-Month Attrition Trend"

**Visual:** Small line chart
- X-Axis: Last 6 periods
- Y-Axis: `[Attrition Rate]`
- Color: Red
- Reference Line: 12% target
- Minimal gridlines
- Large data label on latest point
- Arrow showing direction:
  - ↑ Red if increasing
  - → Yellow if flat
  - ↓ Green if decreasing

### Middle Right: Snapshot (30% width)

**Title:** "Quick Stats"

**Visual:** Simple KPI list (no visuals, just numbers)
- Total Workforce: `[OnHand End]`
- Total Losses: `[Total Losses]`
- Total Hires: `[Total Hires]`
- New Hire %: `[New Hire %]`
- Avg Tenure: `[Avg Tenure (Current)]` years

Font: Clean, medium size
Alignment: Right-aligned numbers

### Bottom Section: 12-Month Outlook (Full width)

**Title:** "12-Month Outlook"

**Layout:** Horizontal 3-column section

**Column 1: Projected Headcount**
- Measure: `[Projected Headcount Change (12mo)]`
- Format: +/- number
- Font: Medium
- Label: "Expected Change"

**Column 2: Hiring Need**
- Measure: `[Hiring Demand (12mo)]`
- Format: Whole number
- Font: Medium
- Label: "Hires Needed"

**Column 3: Risk Assessment**
- Measure: `[Attrition Risk Score]`
- Format: Text based on score
  - "High Risk" (Red) if >70
  - "Moderate Risk" (Yellow) if 41-70
  - "Low Risk" (Green) if ≤40
- Font: Medium, bold
- Background: Color-coded box

### Footer

**Date Context:**
- Period: [Start Snapshot Date] to [End Snapshot Date]
- Generated: Today's date
- Footer text: "DISA Workforce Analytics - Executive Summary"

### Color Scheme
**Professional & Print-Friendly:**
- Primary: Navy #003B5C
- Secondary: Gray #7F8C8D
- Success: Green #27AE60
- Warning: Orange #F39C12
- Alert: Red #E74C3C
- Background: White #FFFFFF
- Subtle Gray: #ECF0F1

### Slicers
**None** - Uses default date filter only
- Optional: One date range slicer at very top
- Kept minimal for clean print layout

### Drillthrough Configuration
**No drillthrough on this page**
- This page is designed for printing and executive summary
- All information is intentionally kept on one page
- For detailed analysis, users should navigate to other dashboard pages

### Tooltip Assignments
**No tooltips on this page**
- Print-optimized layout doesn't benefit from tooltips
- All key information is displayed directly on the page
- Keeps the page clean and printer-friendly

### Key Insights
- Designed for C-suite and senior leadership
- Answers: "Are we okay? What needs attention?"
- Can be printed and shared in meetings
- No drill-through needed - all info on one page

